''AKA Statistical Distance, Variational Distance''

The [[Total Variation Distance]] between two [[Probability Measures|Probability Measure]] $$P$$ and $$Q$$ on a [[Ïƒ-algebra]] $$\mathcal F$$ of [[Subsets|Subset]] of the [[Sample Space]] $$\Omega$$ is defined via

$$
\displaystyle
\delta(P, Q) = \sup_{A \in \mathcal F}|P(A) - Q(A)|
$$